From: Anglerfish AI <noreply@anglerfish-ai.local>
Subject: [PATCH] Route Cowrie shell input through the Anglerfish bridge

Insert one import and a single hook call at the top of
HoneyPotShell.lineReceived so attacker input goes through the Anglerfish
bridge (LLM-driven response) before Cowrie's static command registry
sees it. If the bridge has nothing to say, control falls through to the
original Cowrie dispatch — Cowrie's command implementations keep working
as a fallback.

This patch is an alternative to the runtime monkey-patch installed by
``anglerfish.integration.cowrie_shell_adapter.install()``. Both produce
the same behaviour; the patch is preferred when operators want a fully
auditable Cowrie checkout. Apply with:

    cd /opt/cowrie
    git apply /path/to/0001-anglerfish-shell.patch

Tested against Cowrie v2.5.0 (commit 35e4ebd). On future Cowrie releases,
update the context lines below to match the local source.

---
 src/cowrie/shell/honeypot.py | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/cowrie/shell/honeypot.py b/src/cowrie/shell/honeypot.py
--- a/src/cowrie/shell/honeypot.py
+++ b/src/cowrie/shell/honeypot.py
@@ -1,6 +1,12 @@
 # Copyright (c) 2009-2014 Upi Tamminen <desaster@gmail.com>
 # See the COPYRIGHT file for more information

+# --- Anglerfish AI integration -------------------------------------------
+try:
+    from anglerfish.integration import cowrie_shell_adapter as _anglerfish_adapter
+except ImportError:  # pragma: no cover - Anglerfish not installed alongside Cowrie
+    _anglerfish_adapter = None
+# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
+
 from __future__ import annotations

 import copy
@@ -100,6 +106,12 @@ class HoneyPotShell:
         """
         Called when the attacker has typed a line and pressed Enter.
         """
+        # Anglerfish hook: route to the bridge first. If the bridge
+        # returns content, it writes to the terminal and shows the
+        # next prompt itself; we then return without dispatching.
+        if _anglerfish_adapter is not None and _anglerfish_adapter.is_installed():
+            return _anglerfish_adapter._patched_line_received(self, line)  # noqa: SLF001
+
         log.msg(eventid="cowrie.command.input", input=line, format="CMD: %(input)s")
         self.lexer = shlex.shlex(instream=line, posix=True, punctuation_chars=True)
         self.lexer.whitespace_split = True
